last_episode_to_air.overview: DJ Lance and his Gabba Land friends visit a farm where Farmer Josh teaches them about farm animals, growing vegetables, living on a farm, and even holding a Farmers' Market. Plus, a good old-fashioned farmyard hoedown!

name: Yo Gabba Gabba!
overview:
Yo Gabba Gabba! is an American children's television show that airs on the Nick Jr. cable network in the United States and the Nick Jr. networks in the United Kingdom & Ireland, Italy, France and Australia as well as Treehouse TV network in Canada and RTE2 on RTÉjr in Ireland.   The show stars five costumed toys-come-to-life and their friend DJ Lance Rock, who explore a single topic in each episode through songs and short storylines in the half-hour program while teaching children life and social skills.  It also encourages viewers to move along with and dance with the characters in the program. The show is noted for its indie-culture guest stars and bands, and for drawing visual inspiration from 8-bit video games and H. R. Pufnstuff.

Created by Christian Jacobs and Scott Schultz, the show is produced by The Magic Store Productions and Wild Brain. The series premiered August 20, 2007 on Nickelodeon as part of its Nick Jr. block, and began broadcasting in reruns on February 23, 2008 on the Nick Jr. TV Channel.  On April 30, 2008 the television show received a Daytime Emmy nomination for Outstanding Achievement in Costume Design/Styling.

episodes.name: Circus
episodes.overview: The gang helps Al the Ringmaster make a circus in Gabbaland; Brobee learns to be a clown, and everyone gets to perform. Black Kids perform ``We Love Clowns.''

episodes.name: Bugs
episodes.overview: Muno leads a bug tour through Gabbaland.  Plex shrinks the characters down to follow the Oskie bugs to their underground world where we meet the Queen Oskie Bug and watch eggs hatch.  Weezer performs ``My Friends Are All Insects.''

episodes.name: Doctor
episodes.overview: Toodee gets sick and needs to rest. The doctor visits and everyone helps Toodee feel better.  Of Montreal performs ``Bananas, Rice, Applesauce, Toast!''

episodes.name: Superhero
episodes.overview: Toodee encourages the gang to play superheroes; Devo performs ``Watch Us Work It''; The Aquabats perform.

episodes.name: Baby
episodes.overview: DJ Lance Rock shows videos of when the Gabba friends were babies; the gang spends time with Muno and Plex's families; Solange Knowles performs.

episodes.name: Pets
episodes.overview: Plex gives the gang pet-care tips when Foofa gets a new pet.

episodes.name: School
episodes.overview: Brobee and Toodee get past their fears and learn to enjoy going to school after meeting their teacher (Angela Kinsey) and taking part in show-and-tell.

episodes.name: Adventure
episodes.overview: Muno and friends go on an Indiana Jones type adventure.  They travel through the jungle under Gabbaland and find a golden treasure.

episodes.name: Flying
episodes.overview: Brobee wants to learn how to fly. He meets a new friend on a cloud and they work together to fix the balloon.

episodes.name: Treasure
episodes.overview: Two special guests travel to Gabbaland to search for a hidden treasure with their compass.  Everyone joins in the search and they must also perform a special dance in a secret cave to unlock the treasure

episodes.name: Clubhouse
episodes.overview: Brobee and Muno build a clubhouse for boys only, and they won't let Foofa and Toodee play along. Can you Gabbaland friends sing and dance their way to a solution?

episodes.name: Fairytale
episodes.overview: Lance reads a story to the characters where Jack (Muno) plants magic beans and clims a beanstalk to meet the Giant (Brobee) and his bean machine.

episodes.name: Super Spies
episodes.overview: Jason Bateman guests as the bad spy who steals all the balloons from the Gabbaland balloon art party. Guests: Jason Bateman, Biz Markie, & Peter Bjorn.

episodes.name: DJ Lance's Super Music & Toy Room
Farm
episodes.overview: DJ Lance and his Gabba Land friends visit a farm where Farmer Josh teaches them about farm animals, growing vegetables, living on a farm, and even holding a Farmers' Market. Plus, a good old-fashioned farmyard hoedown!
